$\begin{align}
m \angle 1&=\goldE{180\degree - m \angle 2}
\\\\
m \angle 3&=\goldE{180\degree - m \angle 2}
\end{align}$

By substitution (or by the symmetric and transitive properties of equality), $m \angle 1= m \angle 3$.

Either way, the measures of the vertical angles are equal, so the angles are congruent.
